    "en": {
      "title": "Members are nominated for the Committee on Public Petitions",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Deputy Speaker Mr. Ajith Rajapaksa announced to Parliament today (29) that in accordance with the provisions of Standing Order 122 of Parliament and the resolution passed by Parliament on 10 August 2022, the following Members of Parliament have been nominated by the Select Committee to serve in the Committee on Public Petitions. did",
        "Accordingly, Mr. Imtiaz Bakir Makar, Mr. Jagath Pushpakumara, Mr. Pyankara Jayaratne, Mr. Dilip Vedaarachchi, Mr. Vadivel Suresh, S. Mr. Vyalendran, Mr. Ashoka Priyantha, Mr. Arvind Kumar, Mrs. Geeta Samanmalee Kumarasinghe, B. Y. G. Mr. Ratnasekara, Mr. Sarathy Dushmantha, Mr. Govindan Karunakaram, Mr. Jayantha Katagoda, Mr. Mohammad Mussammil, Mr. Thushara Indunil Amarasena, Mr. Velu Kumar, Mr. Varuna Liyanage, Mr. U. K. Mr. Sumit Udukumbura, Mr. Mayadunna Chinthaka Amal, Mr. Nipuna Ranawaka, Mr. Gamini Valeboda, Ms. Rajika Wickramasinghe, and M. W. D. Mr. Sahan Pradeep Withana has been appointed to serve in the Committee on Public Petitions."
      ],
